        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Silver ten thousand talents.—About £4,000,000 in modern value (see 1Kings 10:21; 1Kings 10:27); or, according to Schrader, who argues from Assyrian data, £3,750,000. The value of the bronze and the iron must have been much greater then than now. (See Note on 1Chronicles 22:14.)",
