        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". This does not seem likely, however, because, of course, the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "daric",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " itself was not in use in Jerusalem in David's time, and any gold coin that was then in use might have received mention on its own account, even if translated also into the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "daric.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " The Septuagint translates in this verse merely by the word ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "χρυσοῦς",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", the Vulgate by ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "solidos.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " Under any circumstances, the coin is to be distinguished from the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "δραχνή",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Specimens of the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "daric",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", both in gold and silver, exist in the Paris and Vienna Museums. The Hebrew word for the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "ten thousand",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " preceding the so-called ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "drams",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " of this verse is the word for \"myriad\" (",
        "children": []
